I watched a couple episodes here and there on TV and never really thought much of it then. Afterwards, I decided to torrent it and see the entire series on my PC for the heck of it. Wow I'm glad I did. You need to download this and listen to it with good quality speakers or headset. The footage and sound alone are amazing, it feels like you're there. It's really captivating.

@Crillie
It makes me sad that you say such things. The documentary, as it rightfully should be, was made by Americans, for Americans, to honor the Americans that served and died during those terrible years. You owe it to them as much as you owe the other soldiers around the World that fought and died for freedom. American propaganda has nothing to do with this and I hope you one day realize your immaturity.
